VOTABLE.DESCRIPTION: Spitzer Heritage Archive - Simple Image Search

PARAM.name: INPUT:POS
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: The position of the region of interest, expressed as the right-ascension and declination of the field center, in decimal degrees using the ICRS coordinate system. A comma should delimit the two values; embedded whitespace is not permitted

PARAM.name: INPUT:SIZE
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: The coordinate angular size of the region given in decimal degrees. The region may be specified using either one or two values. If only one value is given it applies to both coordinate axes.

PARAM.name: INPUT:FORMAT
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: the desired format or formats of the images referenced by the output table. The value is a comma-delimited list where each element can be any recognized MIME-type

PARAM.name: INPUT:VERB
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: Verbosity level, controlling the number of columns returned. Only two levels are supported: 1 (columns sufficient for uniquely describing the image) and 3 (return as much information about the images as possible)

PARAM.name: INPUT:DATASET
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: Desired dataset. Level1 - basic calibrated data. Level2 - combined data.

PARAM.name: coordRefFrame
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: The coordinate system reference frame, selected from 'ICRS', 'FK5', 'FK4', 'ECL', 'GAL', and 'SGAL'

PARAM.name: coordEquinox
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: The Equinox (not required for ICRS) of the coordinate system used for the image world coordinate system (WCS)

PARAM.name: coordProjection
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: The three-character code specifying the celestial projection, as for FITS WCS

PARAM.name: bandPass_Unit
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: The units used to represent spectral values, selected from 'meters', 'hertz', and 'keV'. No other units are permitted here; the client application may of course present a wider range of units in the user interface

PARAM.name: imagePixFlags
PARAM.DESCRIPTION: The type of processing done by the image service to produce an output image pixel. C means the image pixels were copied from a source image without change.

FIELD.name: externalname
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Short description of the image (image external name)

FIELD.name: wavelength
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The instrument and detector used to make the observation

FIELD.name: ra
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The ICRS right-ascension of the center of the image

FIELD.name: dec
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The ICRS declination of the center of the image

FIELD.name: naxis
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The array value giving the length in pixels of each image axis

FIELD.name: cdelt
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The array value giving the scale in degrees per pixel of each image axis

FIELD.name: crota2
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Rotation angle. Indicates how much the y axis rotated relative to North.

FIELD.name: dataFormat
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: MIME-type of the object associated with the image access reference

FIELD.name: imageAccessUrl
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The URL to be used to access or retrieve the image

FIELD.name: filesize
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The actual or estimated size of the encoded image in bytes

FIELD.name: mjDateObs
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Modified Julian date of the observation

FIELD.name: crpix
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The array value specifying the image pixel coordinates of the WCS reference pixel. This is identical to 'CRPIX' in FITS WCS

FIELD.name: crval
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The array value specifying the world coordinates of the WCS reference pixel. This is identical to 'CRVAL' in FITS WCS

FIELD.name: VOX:WCS_CDMatrix
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The array (matrix) value specifying the WCS CD matrix. This is identical to the 'CD' term in FITS WCS, and defines the scale and rotation (among other things) of the image. Matrix elements should be ordered as CD[i,j] = [1,1], [1,2], [2,1], [2,2]

FIELD.name: VOX:BandPass_RefValue
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The characteristic (reference) wavelength for the bandpass model.

FIELD.name: bandPass_LoLimit
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The lower limit of the bandpass

FIELD.name: bandPass_HiLimit
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The upper limit of the bandpass
